               <p>JOHN EVANS. I am a <rs id="t18280911-222-viclabel1134" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-222-victim1271 t18280911-222-viclabel1134"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18280911-222-crimeloc1135">Clothfair</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-222-crimeloc1135" type="placeName" value="Clothfair"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-222-crimeloc1135" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-222-off1132 t18280911-222-crimeloc1135"></join>; the prisoner is my eldest son of ten. On the 10th of August, I had a pocket-book, which contained three 10l. Bank notes, and a number of cheques; I missed it about ten o'clock that morning - it had been in a kind of teachest or caddy, in a closet, in my bed-room; the caddy was locked - it was taken from my bed-room up to the attic, and the nails were drawn: my son had been in my house from Whit Sunday till the 10th of August - before that he had been in the work-house; he got into the work-house and then got away - I have seen two of the notes in the possession of the constable; he sent back the pocket-book and the cheques by a porter.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-222-person1272">
                  ROBERT 
                  DALLON
               <interp inst="t18280911-222-person1272" type="surname" value="DALLON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-222-person1272" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-222-person1272" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I was on my rounds on the 10th of August, and went into the Plough public-house; I received information there, and waited until the afternoon, when the prisoner came, and I took him into custody - I took two 10l. notes from him and seven sovereigns and a half; I told him what I took him for - he looked very stupid and strange, but gave up the notes very willingly; I asked him how he came to do so, he said he was very sorry - he did not deny it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-222-person1273">
                  JOHN 
                  EVANS
               <interp inst="t18280911-222-person1273" type="surname" value="EVANS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-222-person1273" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-222-person1273" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             re-examined. Q. Are these two of the notes you lost? A. Yes - they have my writing on them; I knew they are what I lost - my son has laboured under mental derangement; he was at Bethnal-green for nine months, and then at St. Luke's for a twelve month - I believe he was at this time labouring under mental derangement.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-222-person1274">
                  ROBERT 
                  DALLON
               <interp inst="t18280911-222-person1274" type="surname" value="DALLON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-222-person1274" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-222-person1274" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             re-examined. Q. Did you not take up another person on suspicion? A. No - I understood he was acquainted with a girl in Denmark-court; he offered her the notes, and she refused them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-222-person1275">
                  ALEXANDER 
                  CULLEN
               <interp inst="t18280911-222-person1275" type="surname" value="CULLEN"></interp>
